    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>NEW BIDDER FOR RIO ALGOM</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>British mining company Billiton PLC agrees to buy Rio Algom Ltd of Canada for $1.16 billion in cash, topping hostile $1.02 billion offer from Noranda Inc (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The British mining company Billiton P.L.C. has agreed to buy Rio Algom Ltd. of Canada for $1.16 billion in cash, topping a hostile $1.02 billion offer from a Canadian rival, Noranda Inc. Mainly a producer of aluminum, coal and zinc, Billiton said Rio Algom would give it ''a significant entry point into the global copper business.'' Billiton is offering 1.7 billion Canadian dollars, or 27 Canadian dollars for each Rio Alom share, 2.50 Canadian dollars more than Noranda's offer.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard</p>
      </block>
